Name: Letícia (Evandro Fabiano) Soares
Description:
According to a witness, Letícia was approached by a man on the street who wanted to have paid sex with her. When Letícia declined and walked away, the man shot her.

"Transrespect versus Transphobia Worldwide" research project: Paraná Online, online portal, 11 Sep. 2010

Name: Victoria Carmen White
Description:
Victoria was from Newark. She was killed at 5 am in a relative's apartment. Two men have been charged with murder. The authorities suspect Victoria's being trans to have played a role in her murder.

"Transrespect versus Transphobia Worldwide" research project: NJ.com online journal, 13 Sep. 2010; South Orange Patch, online portal, 25 Oct. 2010; On Top online magazine, 28 Oct. 2010

http://www.news12.com/articleDetail.jsp?articleId=261210&position=1&news_type=news [BROKEN LINK]

Name: Michele (Justo Luis) González García
Description:
The victim was shot in the head together with another trans woman La Flaca (Miguel Orlando) Soto González.

The police received information according to which both victims had been seen approaching a car for some negotiation or business shortly before their bodies were found.

"Transrespect versus Transphobia Worldwide" research project: El Nuevo Dia online journal, 14 Sep. 2010; Sentido G online portal, 17 Sept. 2010; Diario Digital Transexual, 15 Sept. 2010

Name: "Valdir Luiz" das Mercer
Description:
The victim was a sex worker. According to witnesses, she was working on the street when a man came out of a car and stabbed her. She was found stabbed 15 times. Since the victim screamed the name 'Jonie' and seemed to had known the perpetrator personally, the police belief it was a 'crime of passion'.

"Transrespect versus Transphobia Worldwide" research project: Rede Bom Dia, online newspaper, 15 Sep. 2010

Name: Irem Okan
Description:
According to the Hürryet newspaper, Irem was stabbed 12 times to death - from her throat to her stomach. The police found the dead body of Irem in the entrance of her apartment.

"Transrespect versus Transphobia Worldwide" research project: Pink Life LGBTT Solidarity Association, Ankara, Turkey

Name: Name Unknown
Description:
The victim's body was found on 26 Sept. 2010 on the exit of highway Chihuahua-Delicias. Her body showed marks of heavy strokes at the head, and the right ankle bone was exposed. She seemed to had been run over by a heavy car.

Name: (Ademir) do Nascimento Silva
Description:
The crime took place on a highway where sex workers work. According to the police, two men drove by on a motorbike and shot the victim for times.
